This is the right-handed angular bracket used for writing [[average]]s or [[bra–ket notation]], with other applications primarily in [[mathematics]] and [[physics]], for use when inline html rendering is desired rather than {{TeX}} rendering.

This is used in the {{tl|braket}} template. When creating bra or ket vectors, or inner products, use {{tl|Braket}} to save the trouble of typing &amp;#124; (for the pipe symbol), {{tl|langle}}, or {{tl|rangle}} every time.

==Examples==

;Kets

The superposition of states can be written |p{{rangle}} + |q{{rangle}} + |χ{{rangle}} + |ψ{{rangle}}, which is inline with the text.

Another superposition of states: |P{{rangle}} + |Q{{rangle}} + |Φ{{rangle}} + |Ψ{{rangle}}, again inline.

